Q2:
Statistical power is an important attribute of empirical designs in ecology. Using studies published between January 2018 and May 2020 in 5 top ecology journals, we calculated the power of the studies’ statistical tests using the methods of ﻿Ioannidis et al. 2017(doi: 10.1111/ecoj.12461).



Recall that statistical power of a statistical test is the probability of rejecting the null hypothesis when it is false. It can be impacted by the sample size of the study and the magnitude of the effect size, among other things. 




What percentage of tests do you think passed the conventional target of 80% power?
